          "min_app_version": "0.1.0",
          "released_at": "2026-04-21T13:28:08Z",
          "release_notes": "Initial release of the Choice Simulator plugin for Open Choice.\n\n## Commands\n\n- **sim_run** â€” Standard market simulation. Returns shares, revenue, volume, cost, profit, and standard error per scenario Ã— subgroup Ã— product.\n- **sim_sensitivities** â€” Attribute sensitivity sweep. Runs one simulation per (product, attribute, value) triple, stacking all results for chart-ready sensitivity analysis.\n- **sim_combinations** â€” Multi-product attribute grid. Cartesian product (expand_grid = true) or zip (expand_grid = false) across value lists for two or more products.\n- **sim_take_rate** â€” Take-rate simulation. Identical engine to sim_run; intended for population-projected volume and revenue analyses.\n- **sim_exponent_search** â€” IIA exponent calibration. Bisection search over the beta scale factor to match stated market-share proportions.\n- **sim_lock_step** â€” Lock-step multi-product sweep. Moves all participating products through parallel value lists simultaneously, one position per simulation run.\n\n## Features\n\n- Reads HB utility draws directly from an Excel sim_db workbook (or pre-built JSON + binary snapshot).\n- Share of preference (SoP) and first-choice (FC) probability methods, with blending support.\n- Monte Carlo multi-trip simulation with seeded RNG for reproducibility.\n- Per-respondent subgroup cuts and multiple weight columns.\n- Throttle and consideration set support.\n- Eval-lang price formula expressions for derived pricing rules.\n- Product net (brand roll-up) rows via include_nets.\n- Monotonicity constraints on HB beta draws.\n- ocp-json/1 protocol: structured NDJSON event stream with run.started, artifact.created, and run.finished events.",
          "release_url": "https://github.com/Open-Choice/registry/releases/tag/choice-sim-v0.1.0"
        }
      ]
