          "release_notes": "Initial release. Fourteen clustering methods ported from the R reference:\n\n- Partitional: `kmeans`, `kmedoids`.\n- Hierarchical: `hier`, `diana`, `pca_to_hier`, `hier_to_kmeans`.\n- Soft / density / kernel: `fuzzy`, `spectral`, `hdbscan`.\n- Model-based / latent: `archetypes`, `affinity`, `latent_class`, `gmm` (diagonal or full covariance via EM).\n- Ensemble: `ensemble` (consensus via co-association matrix with hier or pam engine).\n\n`segment` dispatches every method block and writes a unified `memberships.csv`.\n`evaluate` scores solutions via within/between dissimilarity, silhouette, and pearson Î³.",
